.\" Manpage for clax — the Clax V2 transpiler.
.TH CLAX 1 "2026-06-04" "clax 2.4" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
clax \- transpile Clax (.cx) sources to C
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B clax
.RI [ options ]
.I project-dir
.br
.B clax_lint
.RI [ options ]
.I project-dir
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B clax
scans
.I project-dir
for
.B .cx
files and transpiles them to C, written to
.IR project-dir /generated_c .
Each class file (one
.RB \[dq] "class Name { ... };" \[dq]
block whose file name matches the class) yields
.IR Name .h
and
.IR Name .c ;
program files (plain C, possibly containing
.BR main )
yield a matching
.IR .c .
A shared
.B clax_runtime.h
and
.B clax_runtime.c
implementing the object model (\fB::\fR, \fBnew\fR/\fBdelete\fR, \fBthis\fR,
\fBObject\fR, \fBtypeof\fR, \fBclone\fR, NULL safety) are emitted alongside.
.PP
The single per-project hand-written header
.B project.hx
is copied to
.B generated_c/project.h
and included by the runtime, so every translation unit sees its contents.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-include= DIR
Add
.I DIR
to the search path for
.RB \[dq] "#include <X.cx>" \[dq]
and
.RB \[dq] "#include \\(dqX.cx\\(dq" \[dq]
references. May be given more than once. The installed standard library lives
in
.IR DATADIR /clax/system .
.TP
.B \-\-lint
Parse and type-check only; write no files. Equivalent to invoking the binary as
.BR clax_lint .
.TP
.B \-\-init-project
Scaffold a new project tree (\fIproject-dir\fR\fB/project/main.cx\fR,
\fBproject.hx\fR and a \fBbuild.sh\fR wired to the installed system library)
instead of transpiling.
.TP
.B \-\-init-sdl2-project
Like
.BR \-\-init-project ,
but scaffolds a small SDL2 program: a
.B main.cx
event loop plus a clickable
.B Button.cx
class, and a
.B build.sh
that links SDL2 via
.BR pkg-config .
Requires the SDL2 development package.
.TP
.B \-\-init-glfw-project
Like
.BR \-\-init-project ,
but scaffolds a small GLFW + OpenGL program (\fBmain.cx\fR and \fBButton.cx\fR)
with a
.B build.sh
that links
.B glfw3
and
.B gl
via
.BR pkg-config .
Requires the GLFW3 and OpenGL development packages.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Transpile a project using the installed standard library:
.B clax --include=/usr/local/share/clax/system ./project
.TP
Lint without writing output:
.B clax --lint ./project
.TP
Scaffold a fresh project:
.B clax --init-project ~/myapp
.TP
Scaffold an SDL2 or GLFW starter project:
.B clax --init-sdl2-project ~/mygame
.br
.B clax --init-glfw-project ~/mygl
.SH FILES
.TP
.IR DATADIR /clax/system/*.cx
Bundled Clax standard library (String, DynamicArray, HashTable, ...).
.SH SEE ALSO
The full language specification is installed under
.IR DOCDIR /clax/Clax-Specification-V2.md .
.SH AUTHOR
Damir Šijaković.
